SIMPLE: unique
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unique
<hw>U*nique"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>unique</ets>; cf. It. <ets>unico</ets>; from L. <ets>unicus</ets>,
from <ets>unus</ets> one. See <er>One</er>.]</ety> <def>Being without a
like or equal; unmatched; unequaled; unparalleled; single in kind or
excellence; sole.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>U*nique"ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>U*nique"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unique</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unique
<hw>U*nique"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A thing without a like; something
unequaled or unparalleled.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The phenix, the <qex>unique</qex> of birds.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uniquity</ent>⟦br⟧
